From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: jianglulu <jianglulu001@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 27 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] orchestrator: selectable firecracker launch mode
 (disabled/netns-exec/launch)

The orchestrator starts each firecracker through a shell pipeline:

    unshare -m -- bash -c "mount --make-rprivate / && mount -t tmpfs ... &&
        ln -s ... && mkdir -p ... && ln -s ... &&
        ip netns exec <ns> <firecracker> --api-sock <sock>"

That is ~8 fork/exec per sandbox (unshare, bash, mount x2, ln x2, mkdir, ip)
before firecracker even starts; the mount steps also serialize on the mount
namespace lock. Under concurrent resume this dominates the
"[ResumeSandbox] configured fc cost" phase (~200-300ms at 100 concurrent).

This adds a runtime switch, E2B_FC_LAUNCH_MODE (see mode.go), selecting one of
three launch mechanisms so they can be A/B/C-compared without rebuilding:

  * disabled (default) - the original shell pipeline with `ip netns exec`.
    Polls for the FC API socket. A faithful baseline; a freshly installed RPM
    behaves exactly like upstream until the operator opts in.
  * netns-exec - the same shell pipeline, but the trailing `ip netns exec` is
    swapped for the fc-netns-exec helper (setns + execve), dropping iproute2's
    extra mount-namespace/sysfs work.
  * launch - a dedicated, shell-free fc-launch helper: it performs the
    mount/symlink setup, enters the sandbox network namespace and execs
    firecracker via direct syscalls in one tiny process (no bash, no coreutils,
    no iproute2, and - unlike re-execing the orchestrator - no heavy package
    init() on the launch path). The helper is spawned through a minimal
    `unshare --mount --propagation unchanged` wrapper (util-linux >= 2.26):
    the fresh mount namespace must NOT be created in the orchestrator's own
    clone(2) via SysProcAttr.Cloneflags, because there the kernel copies the
    entire host mount table (copy_mnt_ns, under the global namespace_sem
    lock) inside cmd.Start() while the CLONE_VFORK fast path keeps the parent
    blocked - so concurrent resumes convoy on that lock right on the
    orchestrator's spawn path (measured at 100 concurrent resumes: fc spawn
    avg 143ms / max 233ms with Cloneflags vs 6.6ms for the shell pipeline,
    costing launch mode more end-to-end than netns-exec despite doing less
    total work). The wrapper keeps cmd.Start() a plain vfork+execve and moves
    the namespace copy into the child, off the spawn path and overlapped with
    the rest of each sandbox's startup. --propagation unchanged suppresses
    unshare(1)'s default recursive MS_PRIVATE remount of "/" - the same
    O(host-mounts) walk Go's Unshareflags path would inject. fc-launch
    instead marks private, non-recursively, exactly the mounts that receive
    the per-sandbox tmpfs (O(path depth) instead of O(host-mounts)), and
    socket.Wait arms inotify instead of polling.

Both helper binaries (cmd/fc-netns-exec, cmd/fc-launch) are built by `make build`
into packages/orchestrator/bin and installed by the spec's existing
packages/*/bin/* glob to /opt/e2b-infra/bin/ (paths overridable via
E2B_FC_NETNS_EXEC_HELPER / E2B_FC_LAUNCH_HELPER).
---
